# Swift Extensions Convention

Protocol conformance extensions for a class **must** live in a separate file named `ClassName+ProtocolName.swift`.

```swift
// ❌ BAD — extension in the same file as the class
// MyViewController.swift
class MyViewController: NSViewController { ... }

extension MyViewController: NSTableViewDataSource { ... }
extension MyViewController: NSTableViewDelegate { ... }

// ✅ GOOD — extensions in separate files
// MyViewController.swift
class MyViewController: NSViewController { ... }

// MyViewController+TableView.swift
extension MyViewController: NSTableViewDataSource { ... }
extension MyViewController: NSTableViewDelegate { ... }
```

If one file already contains an extension for `ClassName`, add new extensions for the same class to a **new** `+Topic` file rather than appending to the existing one, unless they are closely related (e.g. DataSource + Delegate for the same table).
